  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Educational project to expand access to quality, safe and protective learning spaces for children and youth affected by conflict in Salah Al Din Governorate</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the identified needs in Salah al Din (Tikrit), and Ninewa (Al Agha informal settlement in Tel Aljrabia, Tal Afar), the proposed project adopts a two-pronged approach.
First, it aims to provide non-formal education assisting internally displaced children who are not currently enrolled in schools and those in need of remedial education in order to be reintegrated into formal education system. The non-formal education in 3 Temporary Learning Spaces (2 in Tikrit &#x2013; and 1 in Tel Aljrabia) is complemented with basic psychosocial activities aiming at addressing core needs of children and caregivers affected by the ongoing conflict.
Second, it aims to support the return to formal education for internally displaced children in host communities in Tikrit. The support to formal education strives to enable 3 schools to absorb newly arriving children through provision of educational equipment and materials. Support is planned also directly for the internally displaced children attending schools through provision of learning materials (or it can contribute to the Hawija contingency response in case the needs arise). The formal education support is complemented with promoting basic life skills in the 3 partner schools participating in the project.</narrative>
  </description>
